  "body": "I'm trying to run a forked mainnet on a closed source codebase using the following command:\r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat node --fork https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/REDACTED --fork-block-number 11095000 --gasprice \"auto\"\r\n```\r\nCompilation works until I get to a specific error in a deployment file (in this case, I simply mean a file whose sole function is `DeployFunction`). The error is the following (note that it has been amended to not reveal any information about the codebase:\r\n```\r\nError HH604: Error running JSON-RPC server: ERROR processing /root/REDACTED:\r\nError: invalid BigNumber string (argument=\"value\", value=\"auto\", code=INVALID_ARGUMENT, version=bignumber/5.4.2)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there a way to do this?",
